{"key":"processedPost-16297387","value":{"id":16297387,"first":16295440,"last":16297589,"when":1338256388,"utime":"05/29/12 04:53 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />How could I rearrange this setup for all 3 shelves to keep ideal 95% humidity? While still bringing fresh air from above and pushing out dense CO2 from the bottom.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Reverse the flow.&nbsp; CO2 is not like water and will not flow out the bottom.&nbsp; The CO2 mixes fully with the air, so there is no separation between the air and the CO2-where one goes, the other goes along too.<br /><br />Feed your humidity and fresh air in the bottom, since moist air is lighter and will float.&nbsp; Remember, if moist air was heavier than dry air, all clouds would be on the surface of the earth instead of up in the sky.<br /><br />Doing the above will take your CO2 up and out the top.&nbsp; This is how we do it at our <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Mountain-Mushroom-Farm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">below-ground mushroom farm</a>, and the CO2 must be pushed up 20 feet of pipe to be released.<br />RR","title":"Re: How could my full-auto greenhouse be improved?"}}